I'm trying to include a progress bar in Squiffy using -
[code:2qxwir5c]&lt;div id=&quot;progress-bar&quot;&gt;X&lt;/div&gt;[/code:2qxwir5c]
I added an extra JavaScript and CSS file to the Squiffy [b:2qxwir5c]index.html[/b:2qxwir5c] [i:2qxwir5c](added lines in &lt;head&gt;)[/i:2qxwir5c]
[code:2qxwir5c]&lt;script src=&quot;progress&#46;js&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;link rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot; href=&quot;progress&#46;css&quot;/&gt;[/code:2qxwir5c]
[b:2qxwir5c]progress.css[/b:2qxwir5c]
[code:2qxwir5c]#progress-bar {
    width&#58; 0;
    background&#58; #f78;
    text-align&#58; center;
    overflow&#58; hidden;
}[/code:2qxwir5c]
[b:2qxwir5c]progress.js[/b:2qxwir5c]
[code:2qxwir5c]function progress() {
var progressBar = $('#progress-bar'),
    width = 100;
progressBar&#46;width(width + '%');
var interval = setInterval(function() {
    width -= 10;
    progressBar&#46;css('width', width + '%');
    if (width &lt;= 0) {
        clearInterval(interval);
    }
}, 1000)
}[/code:2qxwir5c]
Here is a preview of how it should work: [url:2qxwir5c]http&#58;//jsfiddle&#46;net/94wKr/[/url:2qxwir5c]

I'm probably forgetting something simple, but any help would be appreciated. Thanks.

Thanks for the offer of help.

I've tried calling the function with and without a semi-colon, but no luck yet.

Here is the script file:

[code:1pge2vtf]@Progress test

This is a test of adding a progress bar&#46;

Try the &#91;&#91;Progress Bar&#93;&#93;

&#91;&#91;Progress Bar&#93;&#93;&#58;
        progress()

Here it is&#58;
&lt;div id=&quot;progress-bar&quot;&gt;X&lt;/div&gt;[/code:1pge2vtf]

It shows the &quot;Here it is:&quot; after clicking on the Progress Bar link, but no animated progress bar.

JavaScript runs before the text for the passage/section is displayed. So there won't be a progress-bar div when the script runs.

To fix this, either put the div in the previous passage/section so it's already on-screen, or use setTimeout so the script runs after the text is displayed.

e.g.

[code:23pjbmn5]
&#91;&#91;Progress Bar&#93;&#93;&#58;
    setTimeout(progress, 1000);

&lt;div id=&quot;progress-bar&quot;&gt;X&lt;/div&gt;
[/code:23pjbmn5]
